title: Discord-From-Scratch
description: Architected an SQL database for a full-stack, real time communication website using tables to store user information, servers, channels, comments, and other data, all within a local PostgreSQL database. Also devised SQL queries called by the backend to efficiently fetch servers, channels, and comments upon user login. Inspired by the chatroom app known as Discord.

title: StatsWR
description: StatsWR is a website that presents data to users in the form of character win rates, pick rates, and ban rates based on the mobile game, League of Legends: Wild Rift. Developed visual/interactive graphs using D3.js, HTML, and CSS. Achieved 2000+ unique visitors and 20,000 page views within the first month of deployment, with a 30% user retention rate. Built using the MERN stack.

title: StatsWR MCP Server
description: Created a custom MCP server to fetch data from StatsWR’s API (a previous project) to ensure accurate responses from large language models about the website’s statistics. Integrated the MCP Server into StatsWR by building a chatbot built on OpenAI’s o4-mini model for users to interact with. Developed multiple web scrapers using Beautiful Soup and Selenium to pull data from other websites to assist in providing accurate data for the chatbot’s responses.

title: Wildfire Classification Model
description: Leveraged Python to pull data from APIs to obtain past weather conditions linked to wildfire occurrences. Developed a binary classification model using XGBoost that obtained a validation accuracy of 85% by incorporating factors such as temperature, vegetation, elevation, and soil moisture on a given day. Also developed a CNN using TensorFlow/Scikit-learn to predict the odds of wildfire occurrences, using satellite images sourced from Kaggle to obtain a validation accuracy of 97.4%.
